# WordPress Configuration Management

## Configuration Files
- [wordpress/wp-config.php](mdc:wordpress/wp-config.php) - Main WordPress configuration
- [wordpress/wp-config-docker.php](mdc:wordpress/wp-config-docker.php) - Docker-specific config
- [wordpress/wp-config-sample.php](mdc:wordpress/wp-config-sample.php) - Sample configuration

## Database Configuration
```php
// Database settings for this Docker environment
define('DB_NAME', 'wordpress');
define('DB_USER', 'root');
define('DB_PASSWORD', 'root');
define('DB_HOST', 'db'); // Docker service name
```

## Development Settings
- Enable `WP_DEBUG` for development
- Set appropriate `WP_DEBUG_LOG` and `WP_DEBUG_DISPLAY` values
- Use `SCRIPT_DEBUG` for unminified assets during development
- Consider setting `WP_ENVIRONMENT_TYPE` to 'development'

## Security Considerations
- Generate unique authentication keys and salts
- Never commit sensitive credentials to version control
- Use environment variables for sensitive configuration when possible